<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8">
        <title>Login</title>
        <style>
            body{
                font-family: arial;
                margin: 0;
            }
            nav{
                background: #ff5353;
                padding: 20px 10px;
            }
            nav ul{
                max-width: 960px;
                margin: 0 auto;
                padding: 0;
            }
            nav li{
                list-style-type: none;
                display: inline-block;
                margin: 0 10px 0 0;
            }
            nav a{
                color: #fff;
                font-size: 18px;
                background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
                text-decoration: none;
                padding: 10px;
                display: block;
            }
            main, header{
                max-width: 960px;
                margin: 30px auto;
                padding: 0 10px;
                color: #333;
            }
            .google-btn{
                color: #fff;
                text-decoration: none;
                font-size: 18px;
                padding: 10px;
                background: #ff5353;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <nav>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="/">Homepage</a></li>
              <li><a href="/users/auth/google">Login</a></li>
              <li><a href="/users/getusers">All Users</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
        <header>
            <h1>Login using...</h1>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <h2>Connect Your Database and create a 'users' table to have access to All Users.</h2>
                <p>All Users Button uses POSTGRESQL's <strong>SELECT * FROM users;</strong> query.</p>
                <hr>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h2>Once you have created your 'users' table in either PostgreSQL or MongoDB</h2>
                <h2>LOGIN using your GOOGLE Account.</h2>
                <p>Click ALL USERS to see all the users in your database you have logged into your server using their GOOGLE Account.</p>
                <hr>
              </li>
            </ul>
        </header>
        <main>
            <a class="google-btn" href="/users/auth/google">Google+</a>
        </main>
    </body>
</html>